<v Regina>Yeah.</v>
<v ->They told him</v>

518
00:21:31.174 --> 00:21:32.575
he'd never walk again.

519
00:21:32.575 --> 00:21:36.146
Two years later, Ricky climbed a mountain with me,

520
00:21:36.146 --> 00:21:40.417
in Virginia, so he's a remarkable person.

521
00:21:40.417 --> 00:21:41.818
<v Regina>The will that it would take</v>

522
00:21:41.818 --> 00:21:43.486
within his being.
<v ->Yeah, and the kindness.</v>

523
00:21:43.486 --> 00:21:45.058
<v Regina>Did the near-death experience help</v>

524
00:21:45.058 --> 00:21:47.511
with that will to recover and heal?

525
00:21:47.521 --> 00:21:49.827
<v ->I don't know, 'cause I only, by definition,</v>

526
00:21:49.827 --> 00:21:52.763
I only knew Ricky after the event,

527
00:21:52.763 --> 00:21:57.763
but yeah, you know, that's the impression

528
00:21:58.334 --> 00:22:00.137
you got, talking with him,

529
00:22:00.137 --> 00:22:04.107
that it was his will to come back,

530
00:22:04.107 --> 00:22:06.242
'cause he had learned in his life review

531
00:22:06.242 --> 00:22:09.413
that there were things he needed to complete.

532
00:22:09.413 --> 00:22:11.081
<v Regina>Yeah, and this has to raise the bar,</v>

533
00:22:11.081 --> 00:22:13.423
considerably, to have this experience,

534
00:22:13.423 --> 00:22:14.952
to see where there's an imbalance,

535
00:22:14.952 --> 00:22:17.720
what needs to be tidied up in our relationships,

536
00:22:17.720 --> 00:22:19.990
and come back with, essentially, the same

537
00:22:19.990 --> 00:22:23.127
operating personality.

538
00:22:23.127 --> 00:22:24.661
Like you say, raising the bar,

539
00:22:24.661 --> 00:22:26.263
to try to--
<v ->Yeah, yeah.</v>

540
00:22:26.263 --> 00:22:28.532
It's like George Ritchie really brought that

541
00:22:28.532 --> 00:22:29.499
to my attention.

542
00:22:29.499 --> 00:22:32.003
Because, I mean, I spent many, many hours,

543
00:22:32.003 --> 00:22:34.705
over a long period of time, with George,

544
00:22:34.705 --> 00:22:38.074
and he was one of my best friends in life,

545
00:22:38.074 --> 00:22:41.545
and you know, he constantly emphasized that,

546
00:22:41.545 --> 00:22:45.715
that, you know, you're still burdened with all these...

547
00:22:45.715 --> 00:22:46.683
<v Regina>Yeah.</v>
<v ->Yeah.</v>

548
00:22:46.683 --> 00:22:47.751
<v Regina>What you were before.</v>

549
00:22:47.751 --> 00:22:48.819
<v ->Failings, and, yeah.</v>

550
00:22:48.819 --> 00:22:50.220
<v Regina>And you're still a human being,</v>

551
00:22:50.220 --> 00:22:52.088
so lest anyone try to jump into this experience,

552
00:22:52.088 --> 00:22:54.491
thinking you're having nothing but bliss.

553
00:22:54.491 --> 00:22:55.659
<v ->Oh heavens, no.</v>

554
00:22:55.659 --> 00:22:59.476
<v Regina>Heavens, no.</v>
<v ->Anybody who acts to you</v>

555
00:22:59.476 --> 00:23:00.931
like this made them a saint,

556
00:23:00.931 --> 00:23:02.632
well, you can pretty much think

557
00:23:02.632 --> 00:23:04.835
that they're probably an impostor or something.

558
00:23:04.835 --> 00:23:09.672
And, in all reality, that is one issue

559
00:23:09.672 --> 00:23:11.174
we have to face with this.

560
00:23:11.174 --> 00:23:13.243
I mean, it's wide-out stated accurately,

561
00:23:13.243 --> 00:23:15.378
because anybody can see it,

562
00:23:15.378 --> 00:23:18.849
is that this is a natural draw for impostors, right,

563
00:23:18.849 --> 00:23:22.044
who crave attention.

564
00:23:22.044 --> 00:23:25.522
But then, the way you can very readily distinguish

565
00:23:25.522 --> 00:23:27.257
between an impostor and somebody

566
00:23:27.257 --> 00:23:28.658
who really has this,

567
00:23:28.658 --> 00:23:32.329
is that, people who really have this are very modest.

568
00:23:32.329 --> 00:23:33.330
Like, if you ask them,

569
00:23:33.330 --> 00:23:35.732
"Do little dogs make it to heaven?"

570
00:23:35.732 --> 00:23:37.801
"Well, you know, I just don't know,

571
00:23:37.801 --> 00:23:39.369
"I only saw so much."

572
00:23:39.369 --> 00:23:40.805
<v Regina>Yeah, their experience.</v>

573
00:23:40.805 --> 00:23:41.838
<v ->You know, if there are...</v>

574
00:23:41.838 --> 00:23:42.573
"I don't know."

575
00:23:42.573 --> 00:23:45.242
Whereas, the impostor, whatever you ask them,

576
00:23:45.242 --> 00:23:47.211
"Yes!" or "No!" or whatever.

577
00:23:47.211 --> 00:23:48.195
<v Regina>Yeah.</v>

578
00:23:48.195 --> 00:23:49.746
<v ->That kind of thing, watch out for,</v>

579
00:23:49.746 --> 00:23:53.516
'cause that kind of individual is bad news.

580
00:23:53.516 --> 00:23:55.419
<v Regina>Okay, and then, the whole notion</v>

581
00:23:55.419 --> 00:23:57.889
about someone becoming, again,

582
00:23:57.889 --> 00:24:00.223
so magnetized to this experience,

583
00:24:00.223 --> 00:24:02.992
because they're resonating with the relief

584
00:24:02.992 --> 00:24:05.029
and the joy, and wanting to connect

585
00:24:05.029 --> 00:24:06.863
with something of a loving nature,

586
00:24:06.863 --> 00:24:08.531
that they even go so far,

587
00:24:08.531 --> 00:24:10.133
and I know people who have done this,

588
00:24:10.133 --> 00:24:12.001
who attempt to take their own lives,

589
00:24:12.001 --> 00:24:15.438
just to be able to feel that freedom and release

590
00:24:15.438 --> 00:24:18.509
back into something that they perceive as love.

591
00:24:18.509 --> 00:24:20.645
What happens in that scenario,

592
00:24:20.645 --> 00:24:24.604
with suicide attempts, that do come back.

593
00:24:24.604 --> 00:24:26.750
<v ->Well, by and large, people with suicide attempts</v>

594
00:24:26.750 --> 00:24:28.852
don't have any different experience

595
00:24:28.852 --> 00:24:31.455
from those who come close to death

596
00:24:31.455 --> 00:24:32.990
for other reasons.

597
00:24:32.990 --> 00:24:35.392
But, my experience, as a human being,

598
00:24:35.392 --> 00:24:39.129
as a psychiatrist, is that every adult

599
00:24:39.129 --> 00:24:42.133
that I know well enough to know,

600
00:24:42.133 --> 00:24:45.035
is flirting with suicide in one way or another,

601
00:24:45.035 --> 00:24:47.838
talking on the telephone,

602
00:24:47.838 --> 00:24:49.339
driving down the highway,

603
00:24:49.339 --> 00:24:53.009
or alcohol,

604
00:24:53.009 --> 00:24:55.412
or drugs,

605
00:24:55.412 --> 00:24:58.514
or eating themselves to death,

606
00:24:58.514 --> 00:25:00.050
you know, not doing any exercises.

607
00:25:00.050 --> 00:25:01.935
<v Regina>These are all self-destructive.</v>

608
00:25:01.935 --> 00:25:03.586
<v ->Those are all self-destructive things,</v>

609
00:25:03.586 --> 00:25:06.423
and yet, people full-well know,

610
00:25:06.423 --> 00:25:08.892
or are responsible for knowing,

611
00:25:08.892 --> 00:25:11.962
that, if they continue that behavior,

612
00:25:11.962 --> 00:25:13.162
it's going to kill them.

613
00:25:13.162 --> 00:25:14.430
Well, what's the difference,

614
00:25:14.430 --> 00:25:16.566
between that and somebody who does it?

615
00:25:16.566 --> 00:25:17.734
<v Regina>Takes a few pills.</v>

616
00:25:17.734 --> 00:25:19.202
<v ->Pills, or you know, I mean,</v>

617
00:25:19.202 --> 00:25:21.437
it's a matter of perspective.

618
00:25:21.437 --> 00:25:24.074
God, presumably, is working on a time scale

619
00:25:24.074 --> 00:25:25.975
of billions of years,

620
00:25:25.975 --> 00:25:29.279
and the idea that a divine power

621
00:25:30.989 --> 00:25:35.989
would discriminate,

622
00:25:36.653 --> 00:25:39.775
in other words, this person took 30 years

623
00:25:39.775 --> 00:25:44.662
with cigarettes, this person took a few minutes

624
00:25:44.662 --> 00:25:46.764
with pills, what's the difference?

625
00:25:46.764 --> 00:25:50.433
Now, that said, I will say that one thing

626
00:25:50.433 --> 00:25:53.403
about people with suicidal near-death experiences

627
00:25:53.403 --> 00:25:57.240
is that they tell you that, never again would they

628
00:25:57.240 --> 00:25:58.641
attempt suicide.

629
00:25:58.641 --> 00:26:00.410
Because, they learned from their experience

630
00:26:00.410 --> 00:26:03.913
that, even when times are tough,

631
00:26:03.913 --> 00:26:05.882
life has a purpose.

632
00:26:05.882 --> 00:26:07.684
<v Regina>That's beautiful.</v>

633
00:26:07.684 --> 00:26:09.752
That's a beautiful take-away from that.

634
00:26:09.752 --> 00:26:12.255
<v ->Well, it's beautiful, but also, it's reality.</v>

635
00:26:12.255 --> 00:26:13.716
<v Regina>It's reality, yeah.</v>

636
00:26:13.716 --> 00:26:15.926
And those who attempt suicide,

637
00:26:15.926 --> 00:26:17.727
and do not have near-death experiences,

638
00:26:17.727 --> 00:26:19.266
as I recall your saying,
<v ->Yeah.</v>

639
00:26:19.266 --> 00:26:20.753
<v Regina>are move likely to try it again.</v>

640
00:26:20.753 --> 00:26:21.698
<v ->Oh, absolutely.</v>

641
00:26:21.698 --> 00:26:23.867
They have a continued high rate

642
00:26:23.867 --> 00:26:26.870
of subsequent suicide attempts.

643
00:26:26.870 --> 00:26:29.472
<v Regina>So, if you look at this subject,</v>

644
00:26:29.472 --> 00:26:34.423
and let's just say that humanity, as of today,

645
00:26:34.433 --> 00:26:37.481
you can talk about it on the nightly news,

646
00:26:37.481 --> 00:26:38.615
now embraces the fact

647
00:26:38.615 --> 00:26:40.784
that there is a life after life.

648
00:26:40.784 --> 00:26:42.051
How would that change?

649
00:26:42.051 --> 00:26:44.525
<v ->I don't think so, I think...</v>

650
00:26:44.525 --> 00:26:45.822
Oh, oh, you mean hypothetically.

651
00:26:45.822 --> 00:26:47.357
<v Regina>No, I'm saying hypothetically.</v>

652
00:26:47.357 --> 00:26:52.195
Let's say that becomes our dominant belief system.

653
00:26:52.195 --> 00:26:54.498
How would that change,

654
00:26:54.498 --> 00:26:58.434
or restructure, the way we interact with each other,

655
00:26:58.434 --> 00:27:00.537
in our society?
<v ->I'm dubious that it would.</v>

656
00:27:00.537 --> 00:27:01.738
I just don't know.

657
00:27:01.738 --> 00:27:04.074
You know, a lot of people get motivated

658
00:27:04.074 --> 00:27:05.942
to investigate this,

659
00:27:05.942 --> 00:27:06.909
because, they say,

660
00:27:06.909 --> 00:27:11.909
"Oh, if we could only prove life after death,

661
00:27:12.046 --> 00:27:14.217
"life would be beautiful, everybod...".

662
00:27:14.217 --> 00:27:15.017
I just don't think so.

663
00:27:15.017 --> 00:27:18.488
I mean, I may be wrong, but I don't know.

664
00:27:18.488 --> 00:27:22.543
But, the one thing I do absolutely know,

665
00:27:22.543 --> 00:27:27.097
is that rational proof of an afterlife,

666
00:27:27.097 --> 00:27:28.898
if I could put it that way,

667
00:27:28.898 --> 00:27:33.898
will dramatically restructure the human cognitive system

668
00:27:34.138 --> 00:27:35.539
and the human mind.

669
00:27:35.539 --> 00:27:36.673
And, the way I know that,

670
00:27:36.673 --> 00:27:38.307
is that I've already done it.

671
00:27:38.307 --> 00:27:40.643
I'm in a project now,

672
00:27:40.643 --> 00:27:43.146
which has been ongoing for some years,

673
00:27:43.146 --> 00:27:46.582
but is, sort of, getting ready to come out,

674
00:27:46.582 --> 00:27:49.386
in which, basically,

675
00:27:49.386 --> 00:27:52.021
I'm equipping people

676
00:27:52.021 --> 00:27:57.021
with a new logic from within that framework.

677
00:27:58.527 --> 00:28:01.197
There are entirely new ways to research

678
00:28:01.197 --> 00:28:02.465
the question of life after death.

679
00:28:02.465 --> 00:28:04.034
So, basically, what I've done,

680
00:28:04.034 --> 00:28:07.070
is to devise a methodology that,

681
00:28:07.070 --> 00:28:11.007
by preparing people,

682
00:28:11.007 --> 00:28:13.310
through an intensive seminar,

683
00:28:13.310 --> 00:28:16.422
with this new system of logic,

684
00:28:16.422 --> 00:28:19.482
what it does is, concurrently with absorbing

685
00:28:19.482 --> 00:28:22.685
this new logic, it recruits new unknown

686
00:28:22.685 --> 00:28:26.156
cognitive faculties of the mind.

687
00:28:26.156 --> 00:28:31.156
Now, that period is the point of this program.

688
00:28:31.895 --> 00:28:34.731
It's to instill a new logic

689
00:28:34.731 --> 00:28:37.267
and open new faculties of the mind,

690
00:28:37.267 --> 00:28:41.572
and that is the object of my work, okay?

691
00:28:41.572 --> 00:28:42.706
<v Regina>Mhm.</v>

692
00:28:42.706 --> 00:28:44.941
And the results that come from that

693
00:28:44.941 --> 00:28:49.213
are that it enhances people's analytical thinking abilities

694
00:28:49.213 --> 00:28:54.066
that opens up creative channels, and so on.

695
00:28:55.206 --> 00:29:00.206
But, that being the primary object,

696
00:29:00.730 --> 00:29:04.360
what is also going to happen, out of this,

697
00:29:04.360 --> 00:29:07.096
is that as time progresses,

698
00:29:07.096 --> 00:29:10.067
some of those people who have been through

699
00:29:10.067 --> 00:29:13.070
this preparation, just by chance,

700
00:29:13.070 --> 00:29:14.505
will have near-death experiences.

701
00:29:14.505 --> 00:29:16.373
And, what happens, at this point,

702
00:29:16.373 --> 00:29:18.575
is that when they come back

703
00:29:18.575 --> 00:29:20.543
from their near-death experience,

704
00:29:20.543 --> 00:29:24.915
they have an entirely new way of articulating it.

705
00:29:24.915 --> 00:29:29.915
So, this is the next step in this near-death research,

706
00:29:29.953 --> 00:29:32.656
although, I think it's not going to go over well

707
00:29:32.656 --> 00:29:35.592
with the people who are already set in their ways,

708
00:29:35.592 --> 00:29:37.060
about how to study this.

709
00:29:37.060 --> 00:29:39.897
They will be the last ones to be dragged along.

710
00:29:39.897 --> 00:29:41.464
<v Regina>Always the case, in science.</v>

711
00:29:41.464 --> 00:29:43.699
<v ->It is, it is, but at the same time,</v>

712
00:29:43.699 --> 00:29:46.304
it has the virtue of really working,

713
00:29:46.304 --> 00:29:49.672
and of being fully within rational parameters.

714
00:29:49.672 --> 00:29:51.941
So, what I can confidently say,

715
00:29:51.941 --> 00:29:54.778
is that I have made a sort of breakthrough

716
00:29:54.778 --> 00:29:57.747
in rational comprehension of the afterlife.

717
00:29:57.747 --> 00:30:01.284
And I say that, not based on my perceptions of it,

718
00:30:01.284 --> 00:30:03.621
'cause I'm too close to this work.

719
00:30:03.621 --> 00:30:06.522
It actually is something that I've been working on

720
00:30:06.522 --> 00:30:11.028
since 1963, and was part of my doctoral dissertation

721
00:30:11.028 --> 00:30:14.336
in 1969.

722
00:30:14.816 --> 00:30:18.368
But, it does happen to be the future

723
00:30:18.368 --> 00:30:20.270
of near-death studies.

724
00:30:20.270 --> 00:30:22.672
<v Regina>When will this be made available</v>

725
00:30:22.672 --> 00:30:23.474
to the public?

726
00:30:23.474 --> 00:30:24.541
When are you...

727
00:30:24.541 --> 00:30:28.778
<v ->Well, that's something I can't say.</v>

728
00:30:28.778 --> 00:30:30.046
I don't know,

729
00:30:30.046 --> 00:30:34.116
because thus far, this work's for people

730
00:30:34.116 --> 00:30:37.186
with a certain very specific profile.

731
00:30:37.186 --> 00:30:41.592
Number one, they just enjoy thinking,

732
00:30:41.592 --> 00:30:43.159
for its own sake.

733
00:30:43.159 --> 00:30:48.159
Number two, they have a knack for reasoning,

734
00:30:48.281 --> 00:30:50.467
and analytical thinking,

735
00:30:50.467 --> 00:30:53.236
in other words, they like to analyze things.

736
00:30:53.236 --> 00:30:55.505
Third, that they are patient and persistent,

737
00:30:55.505 --> 00:30:56.939
which is a rare quality,

738
00:30:56.939 --> 00:30:58.875
in the United States, today.

739
00:30:58.875 --> 00:31:01.678
And fourth, that they have a good sense of humor.

740
00:31:01.678 --> 00:31:04.480
But, given people with those criteria,

741
00:31:04.480 --> 00:31:07.400
I can really blow their minds.

742
00:31:08.453 --> 00:31:09.986
Since I'm too close to this work,

743
00:31:09.986 --> 00:31:11.120
after all these years,

744
00:31:11.120 --> 00:31:16.120
I can't make an adequate evaluation of it, myself.

745
00:31:16.155 --> 00:31:18.161
My confidence comes from the fact

746
00:31:18.161 --> 00:31:22.214
that I have given this work

747
00:31:22.214 --> 00:31:24.167
to professors of engineering,

748
00:31:24.167 --> 00:31:27.270
professors of philosophy,

749
00:31:27.270 --> 00:31:29.439
professors of logic,

750
00:31:29.439 --> 00:31:31.174
professors of psychology,

751
00:31:31.174 --> 00:31:33.142
professors of business,

752
00:31:33.142 --> 00:31:35.411
and so on, and so on, and so on.

753
00:31:35.411 --> 00:31:37.147
None of them had a prior interest

754
00:31:37.147 --> 00:31:39.325
in the afterlife question,

755
00:31:39.325 --> 00:31:42.251
and I asked them to evaluate it very harshly,

756
00:31:42.251 --> 00:31:43.820
and to find any flaws,

757
00:31:43.820 --> 00:31:45.187
because before I publish it,

758
00:31:45.187 --> 00:31:48.254
you don't want to be taken by surprise, right?

759
00:31:48.254 --> 00:31:49.425
<v Regina>Right.</v>
<v ->I want to know</v>

760
00:31:49.425 --> 00:31:50.763
all the objections, beforehand.

761
00:31:50.763 --> 00:31:51.573
<v Regina>Right.</v>

762
00:31:51.573 --> 00:31:53.162
<v ->But, the most brilliant people I know,</v>

763
00:31:53.162 --> 00:31:56.732
in my life, and the clearest analytical thinkers

764
00:31:56.732 --> 00:32:01.137
have all come back with the unanimous verdict

765
00:32:01.137 --> 00:32:05.108
that it's real.

766
00:32:05.108 --> 00:32:06.976
So, I'm going on that.

767
00:32:06.976 --> 00:32:10.380
And, what I can tell you is that, therefore,

768
00:32:10.380 --> 00:32:12.615
number one, a breakthrough has been made

769
00:32:12.615 --> 00:32:15.785
towards rational comprehension of life after death.

770
00:32:15.785 --> 00:32:18.154
Number two, the last people

771
00:32:18.154 --> 00:32:19.989
who are going to be interested

772
00:32:19.989 --> 00:32:22.092
in this, or who want to accept it,

773
00:32:22.092 --> 00:32:24.361
are the established researchers

774
00:32:24.361 --> 00:32:25.996
in this kind of thing.

775
00:32:25.996 --> 00:32:27.764
Because, all of that,

